</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>OK, this is a bit of a long one, but let me try to preface it a bit.<br />
<br />
Even though I don't post much, many of the old-timers here remember me as a long-time lurker and multi-class player. *shrug* I just don't have the message-board-verbal-diarrhea syndrome hard enough, or something.<br />
<br />
But what I *do* try to do on a regular basis is check all of the major class EQ boards... kind of 'getting a feel' for what's going on in various communities, and who is most or least effected by what.<br />
<br />
Well, after a hellish night at the office, I came home and decided to go the far more relaxing avenue of reading about EQ rather than playing it before I went to bed...I'm working on my bard at the moment, so you can see the lack of energy helping this descision...I'm tired!<br />
<br />
So anyhow! I'm over at the cleric boards (hey, I have a non-bot templar, I'm allowed), and I find a thread hollering about druids. Nothing new really, for the subject matter,  but since I'm surfing, I go check it out.<br />
<br />
First I find this thread : <a href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=31207.topic&amp;start=1&amp;stop=20" target="_blank">http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruid...start=1&amp;stop=20</a> . Which I read, and examine the relevant links, and think about it for a little bit.<br />
<br />
Then, I find in an edit, this link to a new thread : <a href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=31214.topic&amp;start=1&amp;stop=20" target="_blank">http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruid...start=1&amp;stop=20</a> .  I Read it, follow links....try ...to assign ... logic....<br />
<br />
Then find this one : <a href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showMessage?topicID=31217.topic" target="_blank">http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruid...cID=31217.topic</a> <br />
<br />
*brain explodes*<br />
<br />
Ya know, it's not like we already don't know that druids are ... *ponders a moment* ... 'special'. We mostly figured this out a while back. And I WILL take this opportunity to note that there are some VERY lucid, thought out, and logical posts in the above links! And I mean WELL thought out and locigal! Even by the Glade's standards!<br />
<br />
Sadly, those types of posts are *shock and awe* the VAST minority. According to this, I've found out a couple apparent druid-only truths....<br />
<br />
1.) Absor gets warm and fuzzy thinking about druids.<br />
<br />
2.) Druids should be able to rez, slow, heal, DD, DoT, crowd control, debuff, melle and travel better than any other single class in EQ.<br />
<br />
3.) The Steel Warriors board is even more desperate than Monkly-Business for some SOE-rep lovin (sad, really).<br />
<br />
Did I miss anything?</p>
	
	
	
