	<!-- message -->
	<p>I agree on the warrior comments.  I'm almost to the point of avoiding warriors as group tanks because I make way too much aggro without much effort.  <br />
<br />
For instance, pulling in CYs in PoD, i pulled with harmony on mobs and Annul to get their attention or bow shot.  On top of that I usually jolted once before they got to camp.  With a pal/sk the mob was on them before it got to camp.  With warrior tanking the mob could usually hit me for 3-4 rounds, thats about 25% of my hp on an unslowed mob if he gets lucky, and then it ping pongs around the group everytime someone nukes/slows/snares/CHs.  Plus healing me is an unnecessary load on the healer.<br />
<br />
Seeing warriors in my groups using frostbringer/snowchipper for the proc aggro instead of better weapons is kinda depressing.</p>
	
	
	
