</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Annul magic is a debuff, which are normally pretty high aggro spells.  Pull with jolt.  With a warrior tanking, I have absolutely no aggro problems through pulling this way, even on the occasions when I have to melee.  I'll pull to camp, and stand just behind the warrior so that the mob paths to us.  They can shoot with arrows, or just run forward a little and start to melee.  Because I pull with jolt, the warrior is technically the person to pull first aggro.  It helps a lot with keeping the mob off me, and it helps with ping-pong too.    Paladins are my favorite tanks, and SKs are second.  But I will not turn a warrior away, because there are plenty of things you can do to make keeping aggro on them easier.</p>
	
	
	
