	<p>I won't tell you I'm an expert on warrior aggro but I will tell you this, I group with one or two on a very regular basis for both experience groups and raids. Neither one has a problem maintaining aggro once they have it. The problem only lies in initially getting it - and that is usually not a problem if everyone in the group is not spoiled by being used to a Ranger/Pal/SK tanking. Let the Warrior do the first 5 or 10 percent damage and then be reasonable and his ablity to mitigate and absorb damage will more than make up in the long run for whatever you may have missed doing in that first few seconds of the fight - for the good of the entire group....</p>
	
	
	
