	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Axcell</b><br /><i>I won't tell you I'm an expert on warrior aggro but I will tell you this, I group with one or two on a very regular basis for both experience groups and raids. Neither one has a problem maintaining aggro once they have it. The problem only lies in initially getting it - and that is usually not a problem if everyone in the group is not spoiled by being used to a Ranger/Pal/SK tanking. Let the Warrior do the first 5 or 10 percent damage and then be reasonable and his ablity to mitigate and absorb damage will more than make up in the long run for whatever you may have missed doing in that first few seconds of the fight - for the good of the entire group....</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>the problem isn't xp groups however, waiting for the first 5-10% on a mob for others to engage and for a heal to land is fine, but on raids fighting mobs that quad for 2k+ the heals have to land within 2 seconds on engage which means usualy the 1st and 2nd healers die right after their heals because the warrior is not capable of a burst taunt to get high fast, and their argo is even lower than normal since they will be defensive and doing less damage than normal.<br />
<br />
what may actualy help a lot would be a 2nd taunt button, independant of normal taunt but with something like a 2-3 min refresh, however it's a never fail +1000 argo, it keeps warriors from building argo to the point that nothing can pull off of him but lets him get the initial burst argo at the begining so that the first few healers don't die to the mob for their first heal.</p>
	
	
	
