	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>During the peak of my druid-duoing-MTing days, I had 3k unbuffed HP.  I did this without Virtue or Kazad.  I have always refused to pay for anything more than KEI, apart from donating towards *my groups* cleric's dots and other related reagents of *my groups*.  That's just the way I am.<br />
<br />
Yes, things could easily get hairy if I didn't get a slow off before 80%.  However, with a reliable slow, even that of a beastlord (which is still better than my own), I would have absolutely no trouble tanking razorfiends or cacti, both of which hit for 500ish if I recall correctly.  While I did experience serious downtime with my druid friends (except during the *two times* one of them brought along a chanter bot, out of perhaps 20 to 30 duos), it was not enough to impede the sense of having fun and getting experience.  Sure, most of the druids could've been getting faster, better exp off frogs or even inside the bonewall in PoD.  I didn't say it was the best exp, or even came in at a regular rate.  All you need is massive Dex and the willingness to take an un-rezzed death at worst to see it work.<br />
<br />
Adds?  I could pull razorfiend caves single all day, under the powerful effects of a narcotic that induces both reduced inhibitions and drowsiness.  Same goes for PoS desert.  In fact, I'll take this opportunity to call the vast majority of pulling "difficulty" in PoP 707411y gimp!  In that regard, this expansion (up to tier3 anyway) is soooo easy.<br />
<br />
And please check the "runes and spectrals" argument at the door.  I and my guild are by no means uber compared to Fennin's resident toppers, TMO and da Gang, and I made no claim to being massively underequipped or level 50 or something.  However, I am not looking down from the shoulders of giants; it is not <i>that hard</i> to get to where I am.  I'm about thigh-high, a little lower towards the knees, hanging on for dear life to the giant's wirey leg hairs.</p>
	
	
	
